  "text": "Erased Expression Evaluation. The Cminor compiler (CompCert) is proved correct w.r.t. an operational semantics that does not use footprints. Any program that successfully evaluates with footprints will also evaluate ignoring footprints. Thus, for sequential programs where we do not need noninterference, it is sound to prove properties in a footprint semantics and compile in an erased semantics. We formalize and prove this in the full technical report [CITATION_1] .",
